<bug>
	<id>14468</id>
	<title>Different client and server versions when installing docker on ubuntu (for the first time). </title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Hi,
I just tried to install docker, using the installation guidelines given on your homepage.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">When trying to run the hello world test script I was given this error:
`Error response from daemon: client and server don't have same version (client : 1.19, server: 1.18)`</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">I realise that there is a known issue with having a higher version client than server, but you might not be aware that it happens straight after install, at least for me.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">`docker version:`
`Client version: 1.7.0
Client API version: 1.19
Go version (client): go1.4.2
Git commit (client): 0baf609
OS/Arch (client): linux/amd64
Error response from daemon: client and server don't have same version (client : 1.19, server: 1.18)`</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">`docker info:`
`Error response from daemon: client and server don't have same version (client : 1.19, server: 1.18)`</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">`uname -a:`
`Linux uwp-cookie-machine 3.13.0-55-generic #92-Ubuntu SMP Sun Jun 14 18:32:20 UTC 2015 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux`</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">How reproducible:
I haven't tried reinstalling docker, I'm not invested enough to find out the best way of doing this.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="7">
			<sentence id="7.1">Steps to reproduce:</sentence>
			<sentence id="7.2">1 Install docker: `wget -qO- https://get.docker.com/ | sh`</sentence>
			<sentence id="7.3">2 Run hello world test script: `docker run hello-world`</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
